article.headline: Delaware State 69, Howard 60
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Terrance Hunter scored 16 points to lead Delaware State to its sixth straight victory, 69-60 over Howard on Thursday night. Reserve Tracey Worley scored 11 points, and Jahsha Bluntt added 10 for the Hornets (10-11, 8-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who moved into a tie with Coppin State for first place in the MEAC. Will Gant scored 21 points and went 5-for-9 from 3-point range for the Bison (5-14, 2-8), who kept it close with hot 3-point shooting. Reserve Reggie Bates scored 18 points and was 4-of-5 from 3-point range. Howard closed out the first half with a 12-4 run to take a 31-29 halftime lead. The Bison took their last lead, 46-45, on a 3-pointer by Christian Murphy with 12:21 remaining. Delaware State responded with a 13-0 run, and Howard got no closer than eight points the rest of the way. The Hornets committed just seven turnovers to the Bison's 15, and Delaware State made 21 free throws to Howard's eight.
